msgctxt "mn59:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 59 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 59 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn59:0.2"
msgid "Bahuvedanīyasutta "
msgstr "The Many Kinds of Feeling "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli1.397, sc1
msgctxt "mn59:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn59:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: thapati → gahapati (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn59:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the master builder Pañcakaṅga went up to Venerable Udāyī, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn59:1.4"
msgid "“kati nu kho, bhante udāyi, vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how many feelings has the Buddha spoken of?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn59:1.5"
msgid "“Tisso kho, thapati, vedanā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr "“Master builder, the Buddha has spoken of three feelings: "

msgctxt "mn59:1.6"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral. "

msgctxt "mn59:1.7"
msgid "imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti. "
msgstr "The Buddha has spoken of these three feelings.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn59:1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī, "

msgctxt "mn59:1.9"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā; "
msgstr "“Sir, Udāyī, the Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings. "

msgctxt "mn59:1.10"
msgid "dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "He’s spoken of two feelings: "

msgctxt "mn59:1.11"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā. "
msgstr "pleasant and painful. "

msgctxt "mn59:1.12"
msgid "Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā bhagavatā”ti. "
msgstr "The Buddha said that neutral feeling is included as a peaceful and subtle kind of pleasure.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2, sc2
msgctxt "mn59:2.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a second time, Udāyī said to Pañcakaṅga, "

msgctxt "mn59:2.2"
msgid "“na kho, gahapati, dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā; "
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of two feelings, "

msgctxt "mn59:2.3"
msgid "tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr "he’s spoken of three.” "

msgctxt "mn59:2.4"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn59:2.5"
msgid "imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn59:2.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "For a second time, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī, "

msgctxt "mn59:2.7"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā; "
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings, "

msgctxt "mn59:2.8"
msgid "dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "he’s spoken of two.” "

msgctxt "mn59:2.9"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn59:2.10"
msgid "Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā bhagavatā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc3
msgctxt "mn59:3.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And for a third time, Udāyī said to Pañcakaṅga, "

msgctxt "mn59:3.2"
msgid "“na kho, thapati, dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā; "
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of two feelings, "

msgctxt "mn59:3.3"
msgid "tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr "he’s spoken of three.” "

msgctxt "mn59:3.4"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn59:3.5"
msgid "imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn59:3.6"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And for a third time, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī, "

msgctxt "mn59:3.7"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā, "
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings, "

msgctxt "mn59:3.8"
msgid "dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "he’s spoken of two.” "

msgctxt "mn59:3.9"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn59:3.10"
msgid "Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā bhagavatā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn59:3.11"
msgid "Neva kho sakkhi āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ saññāpetuṃ, na panāsakkhi pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ saññāpetuṃ. "
msgstr "But neither was able to persuade the other. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, pts-vp-pli1.398, sc4
msgctxt "mn59:4.1"
msgid "Assosi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ. "
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda heard this discussion between Udāyī and Pañcakaṅga. "

msgctxt "mn59:4.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then he went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "mn59:4.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako ahosi āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi. "
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed. "

msgctxt "mn59:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5
msgctxt "mn59:5.1"
msgid "“santaññeva kho, ānanda, pariyāyaṃ pañcakaṅgo thapati udāyissa nābbhanumodi, santaññeva ca pana pariyāyaṃ udāyī pañcakaṅgassa thapatissa nābbhanumodi. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, the explanation by the mendicant Udāyī, which the master builder Pañcakaṅga didn’t agree with, was quite correct. But the explanation by Pañcakaṅga, which Udāyī didn’t agree with, was also quite correct. "

msgctxt "mn59:5.2"
msgid "Dvepānanda, vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, tissopi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, pañcapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, chapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, aṭṭhārasapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, chattiṃsapi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena, aṭṭhasatampi vedanā vuttā mayā pariyāyena. "
msgstr "In one explanation I’ve spoken of two feelings. In another explanation I’ve spoken of three feelings, or five, six, eighteen, thirty-six, or a hundred and eight feelings. "

msgctxt "mn59:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo. "
msgstr "I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways. "

msgctxt "mn59:5.4"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ sulapitaṃ na samanujānissanti na samanumaññissanti na samanumodissanti tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharissanti. "
msgstr "This being so, you can expect that those who don’t concede, approve, or agree with what has been well spoken will argue, quarrel, and fight, continually wounding each other with barbed words. "

msgctxt "mn59:5.5"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo. "
msgstr "I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways. "

msgctxt "mn59:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ sulapitaṃ samanujānissanti samanumaññissanti samanumodissanti tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharissanti. "
msgstr "This being so, you can expect that those who do concede, approve, or agree with what has been well spoken will live in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each other with kindly eyes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc5
msgctxt "mn59:6.1"
msgid "Pañca kho ime, ānanda, kāmaguṇā. "
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "mn59:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "mn59:6.3"
msgid "Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā, "
msgstr "Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "mn59:6.4"
msgid "sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe … "
msgstr "Sounds known by the ear … "

msgctxt "mn59:6.5"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā … pe … "
msgstr "Smells known by the nose … "

msgctxt "mn59:6.6"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe … "
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue … "

msgctxt "mn59:6.7"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā—"
msgstr "Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "mn59:6.8"
msgid "ime kho, ānanda, pañca kāmaguṇā. "
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "mn59:6.9"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, ānanda, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ idaṃ vuccati kāmasukhaṃ. "
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual stimulation is called sensual pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc6
msgctxt "mn59:7.1"
msgid "Yo kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyya: ‘etaparamaṃ sattā sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti, idamassa nānujānāmi. "
msgstr "There are those who would say that this is the highest pleasure and happiness that sentient beings experience. But I don’t grant them that. "

msgctxt "mn59:7.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn59:7.3"
msgid "Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca. "
msgstr "Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that. "

msgctxt "mn59:7.4"
msgid "Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca? "
msgstr "And what is that pleasure? "

msgctxt "mn59:7.5"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "mn59:7.6"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca. "
msgstr "This is a pleasure that is finer than that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli1.399, sc7
