msgctxt "mn59:15.6"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca. "
msgstr "This is a pleasure that is finer than that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16, sc15
msgctxt "mn59:16.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

msgctxt "mn59:16.2"
msgid "‘saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samaṇo gotamo āha; tañca sukhasmiṃ paññapeti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama spoke of the cessation of perception and feeling, and he includes it in happiness. "

msgctxt "mn59:16.3"
msgid "Tayidaṃ kiṃsu, tayidaṃ kathaṃsū’ti? "
msgstr "What’s up with that?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn59:16.4"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, ānanda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "When wanderers who follow other paths say this, you should say to them, "

msgctxt "mn59:16.5"
msgid "‘na kho, āvuso, bhagavā sukhaṃyeva vedanaṃ sandhāya sukhasmiṃ paññapeti; "
msgstr "‘Reverends, when the Buddha describes what’s included in happiness, he’s not just referring to pleasant feeling. "

msgctxt "mn59:16.6"
msgid "api ca, āvuso, yattha yattha sukhaṃ upalabbhati yahiṃ yahiṃ taṃ taṃ tathāgato sukhasmiṃ paññapetī’”ti. "
msgstr "The Realized One describes pleasure as included in happiness wherever it’s found, and in whatever context.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "mn59:16.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn59:16.8"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn59:16.9"
msgid "Bahuvedanīyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

